                        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">3. An unsolicited packet arrives from an external server at the Router's WAN interface, targeted at Port 52000. No entry exists in the NAT Table matching this port. What does the Router do?</h3>
                        <div class="space-y-2 text-xs">
                            <label class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2.5 rounded hover:bg-slate-800/50 cursor-pointer transition">
                                <input type="radio" name="q3" value="0" class="text-indigo-600 focus:ring-0">
                                <span>Drops/rejects the packet because it doesn't match an active outbound session mapping</span>
                            </label>
                            <label class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2.5 rounded hover:bg-slate-800/50 cursor-pointer transition">
                                <input type="radio" name="q3" value="1" class="text-indigo-600 focus:ring-0">
                                <span>Broadcasts the packet to all LAN devices to see who responds</span>
                            </label>
                            <label class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2.5 rounded hover:bg-slate-800/50 cursor-pointer transition">
                                <input type="radio" name="q3" value="2" class="text-indigo-600 focus:ring-0">
                                <span>Saves the packet in permanent memory until a client claims it</span>
